# Dojo SDK

The SDK provides programmatic access to the Dojo registry. Use it when building agent frameworks, custom tools, or applications that need to discover and execute Dojo skills.

## JavaScript / TypeScript SDK

```bash
npm install @dojo/sdk
```

```typescript
import { DojoClient } from '@dojo/sdk';

const dojo = new DojoClient({
  url: 'https://registry.dojo.dev',  // or http://localhost:3000
});

// Search for nodes
const results = await dojo.search('deploy to vercel', {
  type: 'skill',
  limit: 5,
});
// → [{ uri: 'vercel/deploy', context: '...', score: 0.95 }]

// Inspect a node
const node = await dojo.inspect('vercel/deploy');
console.log(node.context, node.scripts);

// Learn from a node (returns body + sections as structured content)
const knowledge = await dojo.learn('vercel/deploy');
console.log(knowledge.body, knowledge.sections);

// Get graph neighbors
const neighbors = await dojo.graph('vercel/deploy').neighbors();

// Download a skill bundle
const bundle = await dojo.bundle('vercel/deploy');
// → { manifest: {...}, scripts: [...], skillMd: '...' }
```

## Python SDK

```bash
pip install dojo-sdk
```

```python
from dojo_sdk import DojoClient

dojo = DojoClient(url="https://registry.dojo.dev")

# Search
results = dojo.search("deploy to vercel", type="skill", limit=5)

# Inspect
node = dojo.inspect("vercel/deploy")
print(node.context, node.scripts)

# Learn
knowledge = dojo.learn("vercel/deploy")
print(knowledge.body)

# Graph
neighbors = dojo.graph("vercel/deploy").neighbors()
```

## SDK Methods

| Method | Description | API Endpoint |
|--------|------------|---------------|
| `search(query, opts)` | Find nodes by text, tag, type | `GET /v1/search` |
| `inspect(uri)` | Get full node manifest | `GET /v1/skills/:uri` |
| `learn(uri)` | Get knowledge content | `GET /v1/learn/:uri` |
| `graph(uri).neighbors()` | Get connected nodes | `GET /v1/graph/:uri/neighbors` |
| `graph(uri).backlinks()` | Get reverse links | `GET /v1/graph/:uri/backlinks` |
| `bundle(uri)` | Download skill bundle | `GET /v1/skills/:uri/bundle` |
| `alias(name)` | Resolve alias to URI | `GET /v1/alias/:alias` |
| `tree(uri?)` | Get subtree structure | `GET /v1/tree` |

## Configuration

```typescript
const dojo = new DojoClient({
  url: 'https://registry.dojo.dev',  // required
  token: process.env.DOJO_AUTH_TOKEN, // optional, for publish
  timeout: 10000,                     // request timeout in ms
  retries: 3,                         // retry on transient errors
});
```

## Agent Framework Integration

Agent frameworks use the SDK to give agents access to the Dojo knowledge graph:

```typescript
// In an agent tool definition
const dojoTool = {
  name: 'dojo_search',
  description: 'Search the Dojo knowledge graph',
  execute: async (query: string) => {
    const results = await dojo.search(query, { limit: 3 });
    return results.map(r => `${r.uri}: ${r.context}`).join('\n');
  },
};
```
